The ANC Gauteng provincial conference heats up today, as delegates edge closer to voting in the new leadership. Courtesy #DStv403 BENONI - The ANC Gauteng provincial conference heats up as delegates edge closer to voting in the new leadership. The party’s deputy chairperson Panyaza Lesufi and provincial executive committee member Lebogang Maile go head-to-head for the province’s position of chairperson. As leaders downplay the fierceness of the entire contest, delegates aren’t shy of showing exactly who they're supporting.